Another, somewhat unneces- sarily destroyed some few years ago, stood near Castleton Station, which could scarcely have been later than that last named, and was distinguished by the same sort of longitudinal ribbing as is still observable in what is called the “dungeon” at Danby Castle, a structure which must have been completed quite within the first ten years of the fourteenth century.
